:: DollGuidesToGehrman [ending] {"position":"1700,6100","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scroll-reveal">
You walk beside him.

No words are exchanged,
only small glances, brief and yet they mean everything to you.

You stop at the gates, and with a gentle motion, you signal for him to go.
The Hunter steps forward, toward the tree where Gehrman waits in silence.

You watch as the distance closes between them,
and in both their eyes, you see it.

The pain of endings, the pain of memory and the pain that follows choice.

Gehrman lifts his gaze to you for just a moment.  
A silent nod, no command, no plea.

And in that moment, you truly understand.

This is the end of the Hunt.  
And the beginning of the choice.


[[The Hunter approaches the old hunter.|GehrmanFinalWarning]]

</div>


:: Emotional scene [Garden] {"position":"2450,600","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scroll-reveal">

Your hand hover just above his shoulder, never touching. 
Your porcelain fingers cannot offer warmth. You cannot comfort him as a human might. But still… you try.

“Rest now, old hunter,” you whisper.  
“The Dream will carry on, even if you do not.”

His breath slows. His grip loosens.  
Sleep begins to take him.

Until the nightmare claims him once more.
His shoulders flintches, fists clench. A pained breath. Not quite a sob, but close.

<div class="gehrman-dialogue">
"Maria..."
</div>

The name falls like a wound reopening.

You do not know her.  
Only that her absence weighs more than your silence can hold.


He mutters again, faint as fading memory:  

<div class="gehrman-dialogue">
“Forgive me… I should not have…”
</div>

The Dream offers him no peace.

You remain by his side, still as stone.

You cannot feel. But in this stillness, you understand.

<div class="doll-dialogue">
“He calls for someone I have never met… but she lingers in every word.”
</div>

You do not weep, you do not feel, but still you comfort him.


[[Bring him to the workshop|Bring him back]] 
</div>



