:: Ending_Wake [ending] {"position":"1400,6350","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scroll-reveal">

<div class="gehrman-dialogue">
"Farewell, my keen hunter. Fear the blood."
</div>

The Hunter does not raise their blade.

Instead, they lower themselves, slowly,
kneeling before the old man beneath the tree.  
Their head bows, accepting.

For once, Gehrman's hands do not tremble.

You remain still.  
Just out of reach.  

You want to move.  
To speak.  
To stop what comes next.
But you realize, you were never meant to *want*.

So now, you only witness.

Gehrman raises his scythe..
 
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/bbRzBln.gif" class="StoryImage">

A single cut.  
Silent.

And the Dream… continues.

No scream.  
No wind.  
No flame.

<div class="gehrman-dialogue">
"Farewell, good Hunter.  
May you awaken beneath the morning sun."
</div>

The lantern flickers… then fades, just as his body turns to dust.


You gentky step away from the gates
and kneel beside a gravestone already softened by time.

You do not cry. Dolls were not made to cry.

But still… you say your goodbye.

<div class="doll-dialogue">
"Farewell, good hunter. May you find your worth in the waking world..."
</div>

<img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/221db28026da5fe447bf5cc1927ff305/tumblr_ojjepjxKNC1uutgwwo1_500.gifv" class="StoryImage">
...

</div>


