:: First Words [DollHunterConv] {"position":"1600,1700","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scroll-reveal">
You stand silently, your porcelain eyes reflecting the lanterns glow. Your voice, when it comes out, is calming. 

<p>
<div class="doll-dialogue">
"Hello, good hunter. I am a doll, here in this dream to look after you. Honourable hunter, pursue the echoes of blood and I will channel them into your strength. You will hunt beasts and I will be here for you, to embolden your sickly spirit."
</div>
</p>
<p>
Often, your words are not your own. They sometimes rise from somewhere deepet. It is not your thoughts but rather your design. It is as if purpose itself borrowed your voice.
</p>

<p>
But at the times you feel like you can speak as yourself, you do:
[[“You are safe here, in the Hunter’s Dream.”|Reassure]]
[[“Do you remember your name?”|Curious]]
[[Say nothing. Just observe.|Observe]]
</p>
</div>


