:: Gehrman Dead [ending] {"position":"1800,6350","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scroll-reveal">
You stand by the garden gates.  
The wind stands still. All under the pale moonlight.

The Hunter steps forward, their weapon raised.  
They choose defiance.

And Gehrman answers, his sythe slowly rasing...

<div class="gehrman-dialogue">
Dear, oh dear. What was it? The Hunt? The Blood? Or the horrible dream? Oh, it doesn't matter... It always comes down to the Hunter's helper to clean up after these sort of messes. Tonight, Gehrman joins the hunt..."
</div>

<img src="https://pa1.aminoapps.com/6721/7523987bef812e968be067d31a4ba367d805c28c_hq.gif" class="StoryImage">



ANd in the blink of an eye...
They clash.

Once.  
Twice.  
A dozen times.

The sound of metal clings out like a church bell.
Each strike echoes through the Dream.

Gehrman moves with his experience as one who has fought for too long.  
The Hunter, with the weight of someone who refuses to surrender.

Blood spatters the white petals.  

You remain still.  
You are not meant to interfere.  
You were never meant to feel this.

With a final sound...
steel meets flesh.


